data.text:
Phoenix, AZ, USA

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 33.448376, -112.074036.

The city of Phoenix, which is the capital city of Arizona, is one of the largest cities in the region and the most populated settlement in the state. It is the 5th most populated city in the whole country remaining behind of only such giants as NYC, Chicago, LA, and Houston. The city is the center of its large and heavily populated metropolitan area which is sometimes called 'The Valley of Sun'. Phoenix is located in the very central part of the state of Arizona, right to the southwest of the famous Tonto National Forest which is the largest nature preserve in the state. Due to the specifics of the local climate, Phoenix is known for its really dry and hot weather, cacti and palm trees, numerous parks with interesting fauna and flora, as well as the friendly and open-minded community.

Phoenix is traditionally a center of agriculture, with the later change to a commercial and international business hub, an important transport and logistics point. The city is a very important cultural center of the southern United States, with advanced infrastructure, developed modern facilities and numerous cultural establishments like museums, concert halls, galleries, theaters, music halls, and so on. Phoenix is a city which has been experiencing a great population increase for the last few decades. That's because the life quality and infrastructure of the city are of the highest world-class levels. Phoenix is definitely one of the best places to live in the southern region of the country.
